Peru Stocks: El Brocal, Minsur, Rio Alto, Southern Copper Gain

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-10-14T17:13:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/peru-stocks-el-brocal-minsur-rio-alto-southern-copper-gain.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 11:47 a.m. Lima time.  The Lima General Index gained 1.3 percent to 18,865.76. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose 1.5 percent to 2,481.19.  Mining companies climbed as copper, zinc and tin gained on
signs of rising demand in  China , the world’s biggest consumer of
industrial metals. Gold also rose.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, rose the most in two months, adding 5.8 percent to
2.75 soles. Sociedad Minera El Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a zinc
and lead producer, gained 2.7 percent to 41.10 soles.  Southern
Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper producer, rose 3.7
percent to $28.20.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)   rose for a third time this
week as gold increased in  New York . The Canadian gold
exploration company climbed 2.7 percent to $2.65.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
